          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=B1A79903-5C46-4C69-8AC4-A0082045E182&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Felon-musk-calls-cybertruck-teslas-best-product-ever-here-comes-the-test-42095f45&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">特斯拉 Cyber​​truck 的推出是历史上最受期待的电动汽车发布之一。巴克莱分析师 Dan Levy 和 AlixPartners 的 Mark Wakefield 探讨了特斯拉首款皮卡将如何撼动皮卡市场。照片：弗雷德里克·布朗/盖蒂图片社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001116905"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/rebecca-elliott" itemprop="url" rel="author">丽贝卡·埃利奥特</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 8 日上午 5:30 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/elon-musk-calls-cybertruck-teslas-best-product-ever-here-comes-the-test-42095f45"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p><a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/elon-musk">埃隆·马斯克 (Elon Musk)</a>正在寻求用 Cyber​​truck 重新构想经典的美国皮卡，这是一款外观独特的卡车，采用全角度和未上漆的不锈钢材质。</p><p>现在，<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/TSLA" class="company-name">特斯拉</a>预计将在今年年底推出这款卡车，接下来的几个月将考验他是否能够执行这一愿景并交付该公司三年多来的第一辆新型乘用车。</p><p>事实证明，将 Cyber​​truck 推向市场已经充满挑战，多年来的延误包括设计变更、成本超支和流行病的不确定性。最新的转折发生在周一，这家电动汽车制造商宣布首席财务官扎克·柯克霍恩(Zach Kirkhorn) <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-finance-chief-zach-kirkhorn-steps-down-44e00ad?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">辞职</a>，他在保持公司成本稳定方面发挥了重要作用。</p><p>这款电动卡车的设计打破了传统皮卡的模式，具有三角形轮廓和<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-unveiled-a-bullet-proof-pickup-then-the-window-broke-11574444427?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">防弹车身</a>。一些行业观察人士担心，这种设计独特的汽车对买家的吸引力有限，而且由于利润<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-tsla-q2-earnings-report-2023-9be2b571?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">已经受到压力，</a>开始生产的成本将损害盈利能力。</p><p>投资者押注这款卡车值得等待，并且它将为特斯拉品牌注入新的活力，该品牌的产品线比许多竞争对手都更老。</p><p>特斯拉投资者、未来基金管理合伙人加里·布莱克 (Gary Black) 表示：“Cyber​​truck 非常与众不同，它将让整个系列充满活力。”</p><p>多年来，马斯克一直在大力宣传这款卡车。他称其为该公司“有史以来最好的产品”，并将该车定位为“超酷的未来派装甲运兵车”，它像跑车一样加速，并配备了新技术。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831285?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">特斯拉通过 Cyber​​truck 应对了制造挑战，该卡车使用更坚固、更重的不锈钢，而不是通常用于车身的金属板。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Robyn Beck/法新社/Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> 4 月份，马斯克表示，特斯拉可能会在 9 月底之前开始少量<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-tsla-q1-earnings-report-2023-6b441d30?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">交付新款皮卡</a>。预计 2024 年产量将攀升。</p><p>然而，在该公司最近与华尔街分析师的电话会议中，马斯克回避了有关定价和交付时间表的问题。相反，他表示今年将交付。他还回应了过去的警告，即开始生产新车可能会很棘手。</p><p>马斯克上个月表示：“产量增长的速度将与整个供应链和内部生产中最慢、最不幸运的部分一样快。”</p><p>特斯拉没有回应置评请求。</p><p>提高新车产量一直困扰着特斯拉，马斯克几年前将 Model 3 轿车的推出形容为“生产地狱”，差点毁掉了该公司。</p><p>原本预计在 2021 年推出的 Cyber​​truck，几乎在 2019 年 11 月首次亮相后就开始面临挑战。</p><p>知情人士称，几个月内，Covid-19 大流行对全球供应链造成了严重破坏，Cyber​​truck 退居<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-to-introduce-upgraded-model-s-to-jump-start-high-end-model-sales-11623334024?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">二线，</a>转而进行更可靠的押注，旨在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-tsla-q4-earnings-report-2021-11643162910?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">快速扩大特斯拉的市场份额</a>或提高利润。</p><p>后来，当员工将注意力转向 Cyber​​truck 时，他们很难在控制成本的同时兑现老板的承诺。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="412" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831286?width=700&amp;height=412" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">特斯拉“Cyber​​ Rodeo”工厂车间里的一辆 Model Y 标志着该公司去年在德克萨斯州奥斯汀郊外的工厂开业。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Jay Janner/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>马斯克在 2022 年 1 月表示：“你可以制造出无限理想的东西，但如果买不起，就会限制人们购买它的能力，因为他们没有钱。”他补充说，他担心制造一辆触手可及的卡车对于特斯拉的客户。</p><p>他最初承诺推出<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-targets-u-s-auto-makers-profit-engine-with-electric-pickup-11574341200?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">三层卡车</a>，从售价 39,900 美元的入门级车型到起价 69,900 美元的高端版本。此后他表示定价和规格将会有所不同，并以通货膨胀和“各种问题”为由，但没有透露具体细节。</p><p>该公司通过 Cyber​​truck 应对了一系列新的制造挑战，它使用更坚固、更重的不锈钢，而不是通常用于车身的金属板。</p><p>特斯拉的目标是跳过昂贵的不锈钢外壳制造步骤，不锈钢外壳不需要涂漆，因为它耐腐蚀。然而，它很少用于形成车身，部分原因是它比传统材料的延展性较差。 （德罗宁汽车公司的不锈钢车身跑车在《回到未来》电影中被用作时间机器。）</p><p> JD Power 汽车部门总裁道格·贝茨 (Doug Betts) 表示：“全行业缺乏关于如何制造不锈钢车辆的知识，因此没有人知道他们将遇到的一大堆事情。”</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>贝茨表示，虽然特斯拉在软件和动力总成开发等领域表现出色，但它在车身制造过程中却遇到了困难，而 Cyber​​truck 可能会测试车身制造过程。</p><p>除了重新构想皮卡车的外观外，马斯克还想颠覆它们的组装方式。他设想了一种车辆，其外壁提供了大部分整体结构。</p><p> “我们把肿块移到了外面。我们创造了一个外骨骼，”马斯克在 2019 年的发布会上说道。</p><p>然而，知情人士称，特斯拉已经缩减了外骨骼的野心，转而追求具有内部结构的更传统的车辆设计。一位知情人士表示，该公司这样做至少部分是为了满足安全标准。</p><p>一些汽车观察家的期望更高。</p><p> “它在某些方面是非常规的，但在大多数情况下，它是一种传统的构造，”工程顾问桑迪·蒙罗（Sandy Munro）说，他拆开汽车并查看了早期版本的 Cyber​​truck 的图片。 “这并不是我所期待的巨大变化，”他说，并补充说他仍然认为这款车将“席卷市场”。</p><p>马斯克表示，一旦产量增加，他预计每年将生产 25 万辆或更多 Cyber​​truck，这使其成为与该公司最畅销的 Model Y 跨界车相比的利基产品。特斯拉去年总共售出了约 130 万辆汽车，目标是到 2030 年每年售出 2000 万辆汽车。</p><p> Cyber​​truck 的延迟使其在竞争激烈的市场中落后，竞争对手已经将自己的电动皮卡推向市场。<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/F" class="">福特汽车</a><span class="company-name-type">公司</span><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ford-cuts-price-of-ev-f-150-lightning-truck-by-up-to-17-2cc21c6a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">上个月大幅降价</a>后，最畅销的电动皮卡 F-150 Lightning 起售价为 49,995 美元。 Rivian Automotive 的竞争对手 R1T 起价为 73,000 美元。</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>您认为特斯拉的Cyber​​truck最终会成功吗？为什么或者为什么不？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p>尽管如此，如果特斯拉能够成功，潜力巨大。据富国银行称，全尺寸皮卡是美国汽车行业的摇钱树，去年占北美汽车销量的 13%，利润约占 40%。</p><p>分析师预计，特斯拉卡车的早期生产可能会进一步削弱该公司的盈利能力。</p><p>但特斯拉最大股东之一<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/TROW" class="">T. Rowe Price Associates</a>技术投资团队联合负责人 Anthony Wang 表示，如果特斯拉能够兑现承诺<span class="company-name-type">，</span>这款卡车最终应该会提高特斯拉的利润率。</p><p> “无论是本季度还是下季度，这并不重要，”王说。 “更重要的是：他们能否执行成本和规格？”</p><p>写信给丽贝卡·埃利奥特（Rebecca Elliott）： <a href="mailto:rebecca.elliott@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">rebecca.elliott@wsj.com</a> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/e1f7a12e-412d-41e7-b6c1-3f6c0615c7c1.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 09:30:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/elon-musk-calls-cybertruck-teslas-best-product-ever-here-comes-the-test-42095f45</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/elon-musk-calls-cybertruck-teslas-best-product-ever-here-comes-the-test-42095f45<author><![CDATA[Rebecca Elliott]]></author><category> WSJ公司</category><category>机动车</category><category>替代燃料汽车</category><category>汽车</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>特斯拉</category><category>特斯拉</category><category>埃隆·马斯克</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>机动车</category><category>替代燃料汽车</category><category>汽车</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Legal Assault on Corporate Diversity Efforts Has Begun]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>保守派团体使用许多与扼杀大学平权行动计划相同的工具来挑战亚马逊、康卡斯特和其他公司<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831356/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>埃米尔·伦多夫/华尔街日报<span>埃米尔·伦多夫/华尔街日报</span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001116214"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001116214"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/theo-francis" itemprop="url" rel="author">西奥·弗朗西斯</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/lauren-weber" itemprop="url" rel="author">劳伦·韦伯</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 8 日上午 5:30 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/diversity-equity-dei-companies-blum-2040b173"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>保守派法律活动人士<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/supreme-court-rules-against-affirmative-action-c94b5a9c?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">成功挑战了</a>大学使用平权行动。现在，他们正在寻求在美国企业中广泛部署的多元化举措。一些公司已经在重新考虑他们的努力。</p><p>在诉讼、股东信函和向平等就业机会委员会提交的请愿书中，活动人士使用了一些与进步团体用来推进多样性、公平和包容性（DEI）计划相同的策略。他们认为，公司违反了反对种族和性别歧视的规则，包括旨在保护美国黑人权利的立法中制定的规则。</p><p><a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/CMCSA" class="company-name">康卡斯特</a>解决了一起指控其通过赠款和营销建议非法偏袒少数族裔小型企业客户的案件。<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/AMZN" class="company-name">亚马逊</a>因一项向黑人或拉丁裔拥有的送货服务承包商额外提供 10,000 美元的计划而在德克萨斯州被起诉。<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/SBUX" class="company-name">星巴克</a>董事和高管被股东起诉，称他们支持多元化政策，违反了对投资者的义务。</p><p>数十家公司律师事务所和主要雇主收到了共和党官员的来信，警告他们遵守禁止就业和合同决策中种族配额和偏好的法律。</p><p>爱德华·布鲁姆（Edward Blum）也<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/affirmative-action-supreme-court-ed-blum-100b36c3" target="_blank" class="icon none">组织了这场挑战</a>，最终导致美国最高法院<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/supreme-court-rules-against-affirmative-action-c94b5a9c?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">推翻平权行动</a>的决定，他利用最近成立的非营利组织起诉佐治亚州投资管理公司无畏基金（Fearless Fund），指控针对初创企业的资助计划具有歧视性。 Fearless 对有色人种女性经营的企业进行早期投资。</p><p>公司表示，他们的举措符合法律规定。许多人表示，他们仍然致力于增加劳动力和供应商的人口多样性，理由是<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-business-case-for-more-diversity-11572091200" target="_blank" class="icon none">商业利益</a>和一些群体在美国公司中继续面临的障碍。</p><p>私下里， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/companiesexpectnew-challenges-todiversitypolicies-after-court-ruling-4bf48c1d" target="_blank" class="icon none">许多人询问他们的律师，</a>根据平权行动的决定，他们是否应该以及多少程度地修改他们的方法。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="841" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-828205?width=1260&amp;height=841" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">针对亚马逊的一项联邦诉讼针对的是一项向黑人、拉丁裔和美洲原住民送货服务承包商额外奖励 10,000 美元的计划，以支付启动成本。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Kathy Tran/彭博新闻</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>许多针对企业多元化计划的法律努力早于高等法院 6 月 29 日的裁决。这项裁决主要针对高等教育招生，并未涉及就业或商业行为。</p><p>但这为保守派活动人士和公职人员挑战企业多元化计划的努力增添了动力。长期以来，企业一直依赖类似于大学里支持平权行动的理由——多元化有好处。通过驳回这一理由，高等法院削弱了其他推广该理由的项目的理由。</p><p>威斯康星州前副检察长兼副法律顾问丹·列宁顿 (Dan Lennington) 表示：“公司所做的任何因种族而区别对待某人的行为，即使只是决策过程的一小部分，都将受到审查。”法律与自由研究所，康卡斯特诉讼背后的法律团体。</p><p>就业律师表示，其中一起案件提交最高法院可能只是时间问题。一些公司已经决定不会等待法院介入。全球 DEI 实践负责人安吉拉·伯格 (Angela Berg) 表示，对于 2020 年 5 月乔治·弗洛伊德在警方拘留期间被杀后迅速采取的计划来说尤其如此。在人力资源咨询公司美世 (Mercer) 工作，现在从事独立咨询工作。</p><p>伯格表示，一些高管“从一开始就对股权计划感到不安”，他指的是指导或培训计划等举措。她说，最高法院改变了风险计算。</p><p>福特汉姆大学法学教授阿蒂努克·阿迪兰 (Atinuke Adediran) 表示，公司正在根据诉讼威胁评估多元化计划，这些威胁往往似乎是为了煽动公众恐惧。她收到了大公司人力资源官员协会关于这个问题的询问。 “公司为多元化所做的大部分事情都是合法的，”她说。 “公司可能需要做好保卫自己的准备。”</p><h3><strong>内战武器</strong></h3><p>有线电视巨头康卡斯特 (Comcast) 将一项小企业补助计划限制为至少 51% 股权由黑人、土著、有色人种或女性持有和经营的公司，该公司表示，这些人受到冠状病毒大流行的影响尤为严重。</p><p>威斯康星州法律与自由研究所在 2022 年 4 月起诉康卡斯特时援引了 1866 年《民权法案》。一项经常被称为第 1981 条的条款规定，所有美国人都应享有“与白人公民所享有的相同权利”，以起诉和执行合同。威斯康星研究所表示，它支持促进“个人主动性和有序自由，从而带来繁荣”的诉讼，该机构通过召集几位白人男性企业主作为原告，从本质上颠覆了这一条款。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="503" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831273?width=700&amp;height=503" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">一些活动人士援引了内战时期的一项法律，该法律规定，所有美国人都应享有“与白人公民所享有的相同权利”，可以起诉和执行合同。图为 F. Dielman 绘制的草图，展示了 1866 年 4 月哥伦比亚特区废除奴隶制的庆祝活动。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：美国国会图书馆</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>九月中旬，当康卡斯特宣布下一轮拨款时， <a href="https://corporate.comcast.com/press/releases/comcast-rise-investment-fund-grants-small-businesses-covid-19-pandemic)" target="_blank" class="icon none">该计划向所有小型企业开放</a>。两个月后，康卡斯特解决了诉讼。</p><p>康卡斯特发言人拒绝置评。在五月份有关该计划的新闻稿中，康卡斯特将该计划描述为“从帮助企业度过大流行，到帮助企业及其社区以经济增长为重点蓬勃发展”。</p><p> 2022 年 7 月在达拉斯郊外提起的针对亚马逊的联邦诉讼也援引了 1866 年法律。它的目标是向黑人、拉丁裔和美洲原住民送货服务承包商额外奖励 10,000 美元，以支付启动成本。该诉讼还批评了亚马逊旨在帮助黑人企业在亚马逊网站上销售产品的计划。</p><p>诉状称，原告是德克萨斯州丹顿县的居民，她想申请开设一家亚马逊送货服务承包商，但她表示，除非该公司取消对少数族裔承包商的援助或为白人和亚裔提供同样的福利，否则她不会申请。 。诉讼称，原告“在不遭受种族歧视的情况下”不能申请成为亚马逊送货服务合作伙伴。</p><p>该案寻求集体诉讼地位。该诉讼由包括美国第一法律公司总法律顾问在内的律师提交，该法律公司是华盛顿特区的一家非盈利组织，由前特朗普政府顾问斯蒂芬·米勒领导。美国第一法律将自己描述为打击“腐败的特殊利益集团、大型科技巨头、假新闻媒体和自由派华盛顿政客的邪恶联盟”。</p><p>亚马逊已采取行动驳回诉讼，称其送货承包商的选择过程是种族中立的，并且原告没有资格提起诉讼，因为她尚未申请成为亚马逊承包商。</p><p>在法庭文件中，该公司称她的投诉是“普通民众对一项对她没有实际影响的内部公司计划的抽象和普遍不满的缩影”。</p><p>亚马逊拒绝就该诉讼发表评论。 “我们相信多样性、公平和包容性的重要性，”一位发言人在一份书面声明中表示。 “我们将调查任何法律决定对我们计划的潜在影响，并根据需要进行调整以遵守法律。”</p><h3><strong>工作场所歧视论点</strong></h3><p>1964 年《民权法案》第七章禁止工作场所歧视。最近的平权行动决定并未直接涉及就业实践。但最高法院法官尼尔·戈萨奇在一致意见中指出，高等教育和就业法律中关于歧视的“实质上相同的语言”。</p><p> 2022 年 8 月，星巴克高管和董事被国家公共政策研究中心起诉，该中心是一家保守派智库，拥有该咖啡连锁店 56 股股份。它指控星巴克违反了《第七章》和第 1981 条，并指责星巴克官员在就业、供应商合同和高管薪酬等领域采取违反反歧视法的政策，从而违反了对股东的信托义务。</p><p>根据这些政策，星巴克表示，希望到 2025 年，其各级员工中至少有 30% 是黑人、原住民或有色人种。该公司计划实施一种分析工具，让管理者能够看到他们的进步，并利用员工多元化措施来帮助设定高管薪酬。</p><p>星巴克和公司官员正在寻求驳回此案，听证会定于周五举行。他们表示，NCPPR 并未表现出这些政策造成任何真正的损害，这些政策受到一项法律原则的保护，该原则赋予公司官员在经营业务时拥有广泛的自由裁量权，而且法院也支持多元化政策。他们说，放弃它们将使星巴克容易受到其他诉讼的影响。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="884" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-828201?width=1260&amp;height=884" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">去年，星巴克高管和董事因涉及提高咖啡连锁店各级劳动力多样性的政策而被起诉。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：马里奥·多摩/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>“我们仍然致力于创造一种温暖和归属感的文化，欢迎每个人，”公司发言人表示。</p><p>在法庭上，星巴克及其管理人员还辩称 NCPPR 并不代表股东，股东们拒绝了该组织之前提出的代表星巴克支持自由派或“觉醒”观点的代理提案。</p><p><a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/KO" class="company-name">可口可乐</a>是已经退出的公司之一。 2021 年初，时任总法律顾问布拉德利·盖顿 (Bradley Gayton) 在致外部律师事务所的一封信中表示，这家汽水巨头 30% 的新法律工作应由女性、LGBTQ+、残疾人或少数种族和族裔群体成员的律师承担。信中称，律师事务所必须向可口可乐公司报告人口统计数据，如果不符合指导方针，可口可乐公司可能会降低费用。三个月后，盖顿辞去了这一职务。</p><p>美国民权项目 (American Civil Rights Project) 是一家非营利性律师事务所，在星巴克诉讼中也代表 NCPPR，该律师事务所威胁要代表股东起诉可口可乐。在 6 月致该公司的一封信中，该组织称这些政策“违反了第 1981 条的教科书规定”。</p><p> 2022 年初，盖顿的继任者莫妮卡·霍华德·道布拉斯 (Monica Howard Doublas) 写信给美国民权项目，称虽然公司仍然全力致力于在法律行业推进 DEI，但她已联系律师事务所，告诉他们这些准则绝不是公司政策。</p><h3><strong>令人不寒而栗的效果</strong></h3><p>支持德克萨斯州针对亚马逊提起诉讼的组织美国第一法律基金会已致函平等就业机会委员会，敦促四位现任委员绕过通常的投诉程序，对一系列品牌公司的多元化做法展开调查。</p><p>由特朗普总统提名进入该委员会的安德里亚·卢卡斯拒绝就她或其他委员展开调查的可能性发表评论。她表示，她认为许多企业多元化计划存在“重大法律和实际风险”。 “平等机会是我们的责任，”她谈到该机构的使命时说，“但法律并不要求平等的结果。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          wrap
"><figure class="media-object-image img-wrap"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="639" height="639" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-830072?width=639&amp;height=639" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">可口可乐前总法律顾问布拉德利·盖顿 (Bradley Gayton) 宣布了为这家饮料巨头从事法律工作的律师组成的新准则。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：可口可乐/美国商业资讯</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>民权律师表示，保守派活动人士的论点歪曲了旨在保护历史上劳动力市场机会较少或难以突破企业上限的群体的法律的初衷。</p><p> “这样做的目的是获得更多的政治利益和寒蝉效应——不幸的是，它是有效的，”法律下的民权律师委员会的律师凯蒂·尤克(Katy Youker)说，该委员会一直在跟踪企业计划面临的挑战。</p><p>在佛罗里达州，一名联邦法官去年停止执行 HB 7 中的条款，即更为人所知的《停止觉醒法案》，该法案将限制私人雇主进行一些与多元化相关的培训。法官表示，这些措施侵犯了公司的言论自由权。州长<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/ron-desantis">罗恩·德桑蒂斯</a>政府已对该决定提出上诉。</p><p>律师们表示，这种压力使得雇主很容易因为在解决公平和包容性障碍方面做得太过分或做得不够而受到诉讼。</p><p> “雇主仍然有义务遵守民权法规，”全国有色人种协进会法律辩护和教育基金高级顾问查尔斯·麦克劳林说。他补充说，取消旨在扩大工作机会的 DEI 计划“有可能为某些边缘群体创造一个敌对的环境。公司仍将面临风险。”</p><p>写信给西奥·弗朗西斯<a href="mailto:theo.francis@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">（theo.francis@wsj.com）</a>和劳伦·韦伯（ <a href="mailto:Lauren.Weber@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Lauren.Weber@wsj.com）</a> </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-828197?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">佛罗里达州州长罗恩·德桑蒂斯 (Ron DeSantis) 政府对联邦法官停止执行所谓“停止觉醒法案”(Stop Woke Act) 的决定提出上诉。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：丹尼尔·A·瓦雷拉/迈阿密先驱报/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div></section></div></main></div>]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 09:30:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/diversity-equity-dei-companies-blum-2040b173</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/diversity-equity-dei-companies-blum-2040b173<author><![CDATA[Theo FrancisLauren Weber]]></author><category> WSJ公司</category><category>WSJ插画</category><category>领导者</category><category>广播</category><category>有线广播</category><category>媒体/娱乐</category><category>企业犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>劳工/人事</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>工作场所歧视/虐待</category><category>平权行动</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>社会/社区</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>歧视</category><category>教育</category><category>人权/公民自由</category><category>社会问题</category><category>大学学院</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>企业犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>劳动</category><category>人员</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>工作场所歧视</category><category>虐待</category><category>平权行动</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>社会</category><category>社区</category><category>犯罪</category><category>歧视</category><category>教育</category><category>人权</category><category>公民权利</category><category>社会问题</category><category>大学</category><category>大学</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>广播</category><category>有线广播</category><category>媒体</category><category>娱乐</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Credit Card, PayPal or Cash App? How You Pay Matters]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>权衡每种支付方式的安全性、便利性和优势的指南<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001113428"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831133?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">不同的支付方式提供不同的便利、福利和防欺诈保护。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：iStock </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001113428"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/imani-moise" itemprop="url" rel="author">伊马尼·莫伊兹</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 8 日上午 5:30 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/credit-card-payment-app-fraud-security-3188221b"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>买家拥有比以往更多的支付方式： <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/AAPL" class="company-name">Apple</a> Pay、Venmo、 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/credit-card-cost-fees-legislation-8782d2e9?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">信用卡</a>和数十种其他选择。您的选择可能与购买本身一样重要。</p><p>每种不同的支付方式都提供各种便利、福利和防欺诈保护。信用卡长期以来一直是默认选择。但<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/federal-reserve-raises-interest-rates-to-22-year-high-3c3e499c?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">更高的利率</a>现在提高了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/credit-card-car-debt-payments-behind-decc1a22?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">信用卡余额</a>的成本。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/teens-venmo-uber-amazon-accounts-5043f9d2?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Venmo 和 Zelle 等汇款应用</a>去年处理了近 9000 亿美元，消费者金融保护局预计到 2027 年这一数字将达到 1.6 万亿美元。</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>这些应用程序和服务提供轻松的即时付款，通常是免费的。缺点是这些选项提供的针对<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/jpmorgan-other-banks-in-talks-to-reimburse-scammed-zelle-customers-11669608886?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">诈骗和未履行订单的</a>保护较少。</p><p> “美国消费者非常注重便利性。它们可能不是由安全性直接驱动的，”银行旗下数字钱包 Paze 的董事总经理詹姆斯·安德森 (James Anderson) 表示。</p><p>根据联邦贸易委员会的数据， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/dont-forget-to-block-your-ex-on-your-payment-apps-207358bc?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">支付应用程序</a>是欺诈报告和损失增长最快的来源之一。自 2019 年以来，总体欺诈损失增加了五倍多，达到 1.2 万亿美元。根据 FTC 数据，同期与支付应用程序相关的损失从 500 万美元跃升至 4700 万美元。</p><p>欺诈检测软件公司 BioCatch 全球咨询总监塞斯·鲁登 (Seth Ruden) 表示，随着新的支付方式获得接受，消费者应该尝试教育自己如何安全地使用这些方法。</p><p> “渠道本身并不是罪魁祸首。坏人是骗子、社会工程师和剥削艺术家，”他说。</p><p>以下是如何权衡每种支付方式的安全性、便利性和优势：</p><h3>信用卡和借记卡</h3><p>当您刷卡或在线授权卡交易时，商户银行会通过<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/MA" class="company-name">万事达卡</a>或<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/V" class="company-name">Visa</a>等卡网络与您的银行进行通信，请求允许提取一定金额。然后，您的银行根据您的可用资金或信用以及交易欺诈的可能性决定是否批准交易。如果获得批准，您的银行将冻结资金，直到资金被发送到商家的帐户（通常在一个工作日内）。</p><p>信用卡可能是最有价值的在线支付方式。发卡机构利用交易费收入为客户<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-pandemic-didnt-end-card-rewards-it-made-them-stronger-20fd03c9?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">提供福利，</a>例如现金返还、旅行积分、 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-lounge-battle-royale-coming-soon-to-your-airport-b09cf303?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">机场休息室使用权</a>和欺诈保护。</p><p>如果您不全额支付余额，信用卡的费用可能会很高，而且现在较高的利率已经提高了持有信用卡余额的成本。根据美联储的估计，按照当前 22.16% 的平均年利率计算，在 12 个月内还清 1,000 美元的余额意味着 103 美元的利息，而大约一年前的平均利率为 16.65%，为 77 美元。</p><p>借记卡不提供与信用卡相同的奖励，因为其发卡机构从每笔交易中赚取的钱较少。它们确实具有与信用卡类似的欺诈和付款保护功能。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="468" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831153?width=700&amp;height=468" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Zelle 等应用程序的资金转移速度比银行卡支付更快，因为一旦发件人点击“提交”，付款就会得到授权。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Tiffany Hagler-Geard/彭博新闻</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>联邦法规要求发卡机构对超过 50 美元的未经授权的交易向客户进行赔偿，并允许客户在 30 天内对费用提出异议。许多信用卡还提供购买保护，这意味着如果您购买的商品丢失、损坏或与广告内容不符，您可以直接向发卡机构要求赔偿。</p><p>支付专家表示，很少有人充分利用信用卡的好处。万事达卡发现大多数人在注册新卡时都懒得阅读细则，现在它正在实时通知客户有关优惠的信息。</p><p>万事达卡美国市场开发执行副总裁 Chiro Aikat 表示：“如果我必须阅读一本大册子或拨打一个电话号码才能了解我的好处，我就不会这么做。”</p><h3>数字钱包</h3><p><a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/PYPL" class="company-name">PayPal</a>或 Apple Pay 等数字钱包是最安全、最简单的在线支付方式之一。使用钱包结帐通常比直接使用信用卡付款更快，因为无需重新输入帐单信息和送货地址。</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>您喜欢哪种付款方式，为什么？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p> Security.org 的分析师 Corie Wagner 表示，与基础卡相关的所有保护和福利对于钱包交易仍然有效，因此最好将这些钱包直接连接到信用卡，以最大限度地提高您的保护。 -产品评论网站。</p><p>如果数字钱包允许您直接链接银行账户，您应该阅读保单协议，以确保您了解受保护的内容。例如，PayPal 提供额外级别的购买保护，但 Apple Pay 和 Google Pay 则不提供。</p><p>钱包还通过加密和生物识别验证提供额外的安全层，并且许多钱包不会与个别商家共享敏感的财务数据，例如您的 16 卡号。瓦格纳说，“使用尽可能多的身份验证因素”，例如面部识别码或个人识别码。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=F5C2DBC2-7CEB-4D03-BA48-E58580F05D20&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fcredit-card-payment-app-fraud-security-3188221b&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">触碰支付在美国正在增长，部分原因在于其安全性和易用性。但它比看起来更复杂。 《华尔街日报》带您走进 Square 的一款读卡器，了解支持非接触式支付的技术。图片插图：沉星培<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><h3>点对点支付应用程序</h3><p>Venmo、Cash App 和 Zelle 等应用程序旨在帮助人们向朋友和家人汇款，但现在它们被用于更多场景。它们比银行卡支付更快地转移资金，因为无需等待银行批准交易，而是在发送者点击“提交”后即可授权付款。一旦汇款，几乎不可能取回。</p><p>这些支付方式不像银行卡那样受到严格监管，因此，如果骗子控制了用户的账户，用户仍可能面临未经授权的支付。</p><p> “用它来向你认识和信任的人付款，”Zelle 发言人梅根·芬特兰 (Meghan Fintland) 说。 “他们并不意味着拥有信用卡安全。”</p><h3>银行转账</h3><p>由于自动清算所 (ACH) 转账的处理成本比银行卡便宜得多，企业越来越多地提供直接使用银行账户付款的方式。支付高管表示，只有在获得折扣的情况下才应考虑此选项。</p><p>消费者应该有选择性地与商家分享他们的银行信息，因为电汇没有与银行卡相同的保护保证。</p><p>如果企业要求直接银行转账而不是银行卡付款，那么选择速度较慢的选项而不是 Zelle 等较新的即时方法可能是最好的选择。 ACH 转账通常需要几天时间才能结算，因此您还有几天时间尝试在资金离开您的账户之前停止交易。</p><p> BioCatch 的 Ruden 表示：“速度越慢，获得追索权的可能性就越大。”</p><p>写信给伊玛尼·莫伊兹： <a href="mailto:imani.moise@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">imani.moise@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 09:30:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/credit-card- payment-app-fraud-security-3188221b</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/credit-card- payment-app-fraud-security-3188221b<author><![CDATA[Imani Moise]]></author><category> WSJ生活工作</category><category>信用类型/服务</category><category>信用卡</category><category>银行/信贷</category><category>金融服务</category><category>金融科技</category><category>移动支付系统</category><category>电子支付系统</category><category>技术</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>欺诈罪</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>欺诈罪</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>信用类型</category><category>服务</category><category>信用卡</category><category>银行业</category><category>信用</category><category>金融服务</category><category>金融科技</category><category>移动支付系统</category><category>电子支付系统</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘First to the Front’ Review: A Leading Lady of Journalism]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>一位编辑给她贴上了“刺刀边境通讯员”的标签，因为她通常是最先到达战区的人之一。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB12770427345856314244904590126000121988496"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-830547?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 1955 年，迪基·查佩尔 (Dickey Chapelle) 拍摄海军陆战队照片。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：威斯康星历史学会</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB12770427345856314244904590126000121988496"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"><span class="author" itemprop="name">夏洛特·格雷</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 7 日下午 5:58 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/first-to-the-front-review-a-leading-lady-of-journalism-abe61786"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>迪基·查佩尔的一生读起来就像一部好莱坞电影。一位戴着珍珠耳环的摄影记者和战地记者打破了所有刻板印象，打破了故事并超越了美国海军陆战队的勇敢；她受到自由战士的尊敬，受到五角大楼高层的咨询，并在退休担任名誉教授之前被授予总统自由勋章。</p><p>这一切都发生在真正的迪基·查佩尔身上——1918 年出生于密尔沃基，原名乔吉特·迈耶——除了自由勋章和教授职位。相反，查佩尔于 1965 年在越南随海军陆战队排巡逻时被杀，很快就被人们遗忘了。她的许多报告和快讯从未付诸出版，要么是因为她找不到新闻媒体，要么是因为审查制度压制了它们。她爱国、有原则、坚韧到鲁莽的地步。正如洛里莎·莱因哈特（Lorissa Rinehart）在《率先上前线》中所描述的那样，查佩尔坚持用自己的眼睛看每个故事，从士兵而不是将军的角度来描述事件。 “按理说，”莱因哈特女士写道，“迪基·查佩尔应该是一个家喻户晓的名字。” </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/schemas/9ff4b76d-bdcb-46cd-935f-e30ea391114c.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p>查佩尔从小就痴迷于飞行的刺激，她是 1934 年被麻省理工学院航空工程班录取的三名女性之一。她很聪明，但更重要的是，她勇敢无畏。因考试不及格而退学后（她更喜欢看飞机而不是设计飞机），她在当地的一个空中马戏团工作，这样她就可以参加飞行课程。她很快意识到有关航展的文章有市场，在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/NYT" class="company-name">《纽约时报》</a>刊登了她的一篇报道后，霍华德·休斯的横贯大陆和西部航空（后来的环球航空）的宣传主管为她提供了一份助理的工作。</p><p> 1939 年欧洲爆发战争时，莱因哈特女士告诉我们，“她看到世界在历史时刻的悬崖上摇摇欲坠，并且知道她必须成为其中的一部分。”她的志向是成为一名摄影记者，因此她报名参加环球航空公司的宣传摄影师课程。安东尼·查佩尔（Anthony Chapelle）年龄是她的两倍，很有魅力，善于交际，是一位好老师，迪基爱上了他。两人于1940年结婚。</p><p>迪基·查佩尔 (Dickey Chapelle) 第一次有机会报道军事演习是在 1942 年，当时《Look》杂志派她去拍摄第 14 步兵团在巴拿马丛林中的训练。她证明了自己和学员一样坚韧和勇敢，扛着自己沉重的摄影设备穿过令人窒息的潮湿和蚊子密布的环境。但国内的军事审查机构阻止她的照片出现在印刷品上，理由是这些照片对国家安全构成威胁。</p><p>她的下一次前线机会是 1945 年，当时她收到了前往太平洋战区的委托和官方许可。在那之前，还没有女性摄影师被允许进入战区；她首先加入了海军护理队，负责将伤员疏散到美国医院。她很快就挤到珍珠港，然后到达硫磺岛，在那里她在战斗中掩护海军陆战队。当她拍摄伤员被装上医院船并将镜头对准那些流血过多而死的年轻人时，她磨练了将他们的故事编织成扣人心弦的故事所需的技巧和钢铁般的超然态度。</p><p>到现在为止，查佩尔已经彻底迷上了战争报道。她的报道重点关注生活被战争摧残的士兵、水手、护士、飞行员、游击队员和难民。她告诉她的军事护送人员，她的任务之一就是向家乡传达献血的重要性。正如莱因哈特女士所说，这立即让她受到了所有人的喜爱，“从最闪亮的黄铜纽扣到最肮脏的靴子”。然而，尽管她被命令留在医院船上，但她成功捕捉到了这一动作，导致她的记者证被撤销。她的作品很少出版。</p><p>战后，她说服贵格会派她去东欧进行一次长途旅行，拍摄因战争及其后果（饥饿、无家可归、疾病）而遭受创伤的家庭，特别是儿童。几年之内，《国家地理》等著名出版物就开始使用她的照片和故事。 1956 年，在报道匈牙利革命时，她被捕并入狱六周，其中五周被单独监禁。莱因哈特女士写道，这段经历让她在心理上受到了伤害，并将她对极权主义政权的敌意转变为“击退共产主义浪潮”并讲述“其他人为自由而奋斗的故事”的强烈决心。</p><p>查佩尔的使命将导致她与阿尔及利亚叛乱分子一起参与反对法国统治的斗争，并与菲德尔·卡斯特罗一起</p>古巴革命时期的游击队。一位编辑给她贴上了“刺刀边境通讯员”的标签，因为她通常是第一批到达前线的人。 1961 年，她开始报道美国军队击退越共的努力。 1965 年她去世时，她对美国军事领导人无法理解游击战以及中央情报局在非法扩大战争中的共谋感到愤怒。但军事审查制度阻止她报道她的愤怒。 “也许迪基应该知道她即将走进美国历史上最黑暗的时期之一，”莱因哈特女士写道。但她无法回头，因为“她自己的天真、恐惧或渴望相信美国仍然可以成为自由的灯塔”。<p></p><p> 《先锋》讲述了一个非凡的故事，充满戏剧性和许多可怕的细节。由于没有脚注，很难判断其中许多细节的来源。相反，作者列出了每一章的主要来源，几乎所有这些都是查佩尔自己的笔记、信件、文章和她的自传（最初的标题是“女人在这里做什么？”）。因此，这个故事几乎完全是从查佩尔的角度来讲述的，（大概）是作者的华丽色彩，但没有来自查佩尔的编辑、同行或联系人的评论——他们无疑钦佩她的作品，但可能被她的冒险欲望所激怒。和她的传教士热情。然而，对于那些成为她报道焦点的人来说，迪基·查佩尔始终是一位英雄。她在密尔沃基举行的葬礼是美国女记者首次在战斗中身亡，一名海军陆战队仪仗队盛装出席。</p><p><em>格雷女士是《热情的母亲，强大的儿子：珍妮·杰罗姆·丘吉尔和萨拉·德拉诺·罗斯福的一生》一书的作者，该书将于 9 月出版。</em></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 21:58:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/first-to-the-front-review-a-leading-lady-of-journalism-abe61786</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/first-to-the-front-review-a-leading-lady-of-journalism-abe61786<category>艺术</category><category>图书</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>艺术/娱乐</category><category>摄影</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 排除过滤器</category><category>评论</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>观点</category><category>艺术</category><category>图书</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>艺术</category><category>娱乐</category><category>摄影</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>c&amp;e 排除过滤器</category><category>评论</category><category>观点</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Chrome Dreams’ by Neil Young Review: From Bootleg to Banner Release]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>这位音乐家的新专辑是一张在 70 年代录制发行但后来被放弃的合集，巩固了他在该十年最佳创作歌手中的地位。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB12165777042486313942804590136211558677190"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-830590?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">尼尔·杨</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：丹尼·克林奇</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB12165777042486313942804590136211558677190"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"><span class="author" itemprop="name">马克·理查森</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 7 日下午 5:50 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chrome-dreams-by-neil-young-review-from-bootleg-to-banner-release-47e258ce"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>某种类型的音乐痴迷者——比如那些不断进入前五名名单并在 2000 年电影《高保真》中的角色中认出自己的人——喜欢争论特定十年中最好的乐队或表演。 60 年代的披头士是常见的选择，80 年代的 Prince 也是如此。在 70 年代，也就是黑胶唱片时代的鼎盛时期，竞争尤其激烈，当时音乐处于流行文化对话的中心。史蒂夫·旺德？绝佳的选择，可能是最合乎逻辑的。大卫·鲍伊 ？这也是合理的，特别是考虑到他的地位在过去 15 年里不断增长。或者 Led Zeppelin 乐队，一支改变了硬摇滚声音的乐队？或者甚至是灵魂乐歌手艾尔·格林（Al Green），一位一致性大师，他在这十年的前七张专辑中几乎没有一首弱歌？但我们还必须考虑尼尔·杨。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><figure class="media-object-image img-wrap"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="639" height="639" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-830580?width=639&amp;height=639" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"></figcaption></figure></div><p>在那十年里，这位加拿大创作型歌手发行了八张录音室专辑，并与斯蒂芬·斯蒂尔斯 (Stephen Stills) 合作发行了另一张录音室唱片。他与 Crosby、Stills 和 Nash 一起录制；他发行了一张现场专辑“Time Fades Away”（1973），其中充满了全新的歌曲，其中许多歌曲都很精彩，而另一张“Live Rust”（1979）则被认为是有史以来最好的音乐会摇滚专辑之一制成。纯粹根据当时的作品来看，这是十年来令人印象深刻的作品，足以让杨先生竞选 70 年代最重要的艺术家。但这些官方发布的消息并不是故事的全部。</p><p> Young 先生在 70 年代不断录音，并根据本能做出决定，在最后一刻取消项目，原因只有他自己知道。这一时期的几张黑胶唱片准备发行，然后就被放弃了，对于铁杆粉丝来说，这些默默无闻的唱片已成为传奇。在过去的几年里，作为尼尔杨档案项目的一部分，杨先生发行了几张这样的“丢失的专辑”。其中最新的《Chrome Dreams》（Reprise）于周五推出，最初考虑于 1977 年发行，后来被盗版。这是一本非常棒的歌曲集，如果以这种形式发行，将会被认为是杨先生目录中的上层歌曲。</p><p>多年来，“Chrome Dreams”中的所有歌曲最终都以这样或那样的形式问世。有些被重新录制或配音以供以后发行，而另一些则以与以后发行的形式相同的形式出现在此处。唱片最早的部分有着最熟悉的标题，但“Chrome Dreams”的顺序让它们听起来很新鲜。该专辑以“Pocahontas”开场，这首歌后来成为“Rust Never Sleeps”的亮点，并被评为杨先生职业生涯中最美丽的歌曲。在“Rust”中，这首歌沐浴在混响中，伴随着和声和音效的光环。这与此处找到的杨先生的声音和吉他的录音相同，但有额外的制作。在《Chrome Dreams》的原始录音中，这种赤裸裸的风格给这首歌增添了额外的孤独和忧郁感。</p><p>接下来是安静的“爱的意志”，它几乎不超过耳语；然后是忧郁的“伯利恒之星”，它让人想起杨先生70年代初期作品中乡村风格的节奏，为异常柔和的开场三联画画上了圆满的句号。这种遐想被八分钟的“Like a Hurricane”打断，这是一首中速摇滚歌曲，旨在展示 Young 先生嘈杂而棘手的电吉他主音。这三首歌以不同的顺序打开了杨先生的《American Stars &#39;n Bars》的第二面，这张专辑是他发行的，而不是《Chrome Dreams》，但在开场《Pocahontas》之后听到它们提升了材料，推动可见杨先生在这个时代的歌曲创作有多么强大。</p><p>唱片的后半段从具有古老民谣味道的《肯尼迪船长》开始，后来收录在《鹰与鸽子》（1980）中；华丽的钢琴民谣“Stringman”直到 1993 年才发行，当时 Young 先生发行了他的“MTV Unplugged”表演录音；到“Sedan Delivery”的慢速蓝调版本，该版本出现在“Rust Never Sleeps”的另一张录音中。最后一首之前从未发行过的歌曲的风格更加沉重，带有原始的吉他连复段，让人想起 Link Wray 的“Rumble”。 “Powderfinger”是另一首出现在“Rust”中全乐队改编的歌曲，是 Young 的独奏。虽然它没有其他版本的招摇，但它将杨先生可爱的旋律置于前台，产生了令人心酸的效果。</p><p>尽管杨先生是摇滚史上最敏锐的词曲作者之一，但他也是一位拼贴艺术家，通过以特定并置的方式组合作品来制作精彩的专辑。 “从来没有人提到过我们正在制作一张专辑，”杨先生的伴奏乐队 Crazy Horse 的吉他手弗兰克·桑佩德罗 (Frank Sampedro) 谈到这一时期时说道。 “我们只是演奏和录音。”如果 Young 先生在 1977 年按此顺序发行这些歌曲，会对他的职业生涯产生影响吗？这很难说，但一张如此强大的唱片被搁置，然后被拆成碎片，这一事实充分说明了杨先生在那些令人兴奋的日子里有多少想法。</p><p class="articleTagLine"> -先生。理查森是《华尔街日报》的摇滚和流行音乐评论家。在 Twitter 上关注他@MarkRichardson。</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 21:50:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/chrome-dreams-by-neil-young-review-from-bootleg-to-banner-release-47e258ce</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/chrome-dreams-by-neil-young-review-from-bootleg-to-banner-release-47e258ce<category>艺术评论</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>音乐会</category><category>艺术/娱乐</category><category>音乐</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 排除过滤器</category><category>评论</category><category>艺术回顾</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>音乐会</category><category>艺术</category><category>娱乐</category><category>音乐</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>c&amp;e 排除过滤器</category><category>评论</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[A Real-Estate Haven Turns Perilous With $1 Trillion Coming Due]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>公寓楼的价值多年来一直上涨，但飙升的利率现在笼罩着该行业的业主<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-830485/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="随着租金稳步上涨，投资者抬高了多户住宅的价格。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>随着租金稳步上涨，投资者抬高了多户住宅的价格。理查德·B·莱文/祖玛出版社<span>理查德·B·莱文/祖玛出版社</span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001112088"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001112088"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/konrad-putzier" itemprop="url" rel="author">康拉德·普齐尔</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/will-parker" itemprop="url" rel="author">威尔·帕克</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 7 日上午 5:30 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/a-real-estate-haven-turns-perilous-with-roughly-1-trillion-coming-due-74d20528"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>长期以来被认为是房地产天堂的公寓楼正在成为陷入困境的商业地产领域的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/houston-apartment-owner-loses-3-200-units-to-foreclosure-as-multifamily-feels-the-heat-fb3d0e75?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">下一个主要麻烦点</a>。</p><p>多年来，受租金稳步上涨和巨额回报前景的吸引，投资者不断抬高多户住宅的价格。许多人承担了过多的债务，期望能够以足够快的速度提高租金来偿还债务。</p><p>与受到远程工作和电子商务严重打击的写字楼和商场不同，出租公寓的空置率较低。公寓行业的主要问题不是缺乏需求——自 2020 年以来租金飙升——而是<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/investors-bet-that-high-rates-will-linger-61cdaeb7?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">利率</a>。</p><p>去年债务成本的突然飙升现在有可能使全国许多多户家庭业主破产。数据公司<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/CSGP" class="">CoStar</a>的数据显示，继去年上涨 25% 后，截至 6 月份的一年中，公寓楼价值下降了 14% <span class="company-name-type">。</span>这一下降幅度与写字楼价值的下降幅度大致相同。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-830530?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">许多公寓楼投资者承担了过多的债务，期望他们能够足够快地提高租金来偿还债务。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：大卫·保罗·莫里斯/彭博新闻</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>多户住宅类别的抵押贷款拖欠率较低，但仍在增加。借贷成本翻了一番，租金增长放缓，建筑费用上升。数据提供商特雷普今年早些时候发现，在面临违约风险的商业抵押贷款中，一类出租公寓债务占很大比例。</p><p>资深房地产金融高管、Blackstone 房地产债务业务前创始成员、Mack Real Estate Credit Strategies 前管理合伙人 Peter Sotoloff 表示，公寓房东面临着“氢弹情景”。<br><br>根据抵押贷款银行家协会的数据，未偿还的多户抵押贷款在过去十年中增加了一倍多，达到约 2 万亿美元。特雷普表示，这几乎是办公室债务的两倍。该数据提供商补充说，9807 亿美元的多户家庭债务预计将在 2023 年至 2027 年间到期。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><img width="600" height="800" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-830785?width=600" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> “每个人都专注于办公室，”索托洛夫说。他补充说，公寓违约的风险“是一个非常大的问题，但没有得到应有的关注。”</p><p>洛杉矶、休斯顿和旧金山的多户住宅业主拖欠了数千套公寓的贷款。据一位知情人士透露<span class="company-name-type">，</span>全球最大的另类资产管理公司<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/BX" class="">Blackstone</a>正在为曼哈顿 11 栋公寓楼的相关抵押贷款提供特殊服务。 Blackstone 的一位发言人表示，这些建筑存在独特的问题，“不能代表我们在更广泛的租赁住房组合中看到的实力。”</p><p>公寓楼被誉为风险较低的商业房地产投资。即使在经济衰退时期，包括2008-2009年金融危机期间房地产市场崩溃时，它们的表现也相对较好。人们总是需要一个地方居住，在危机时期，前房主会涌入租赁市场。</p><p>通货膨胀还使房东能够比平时提高租金，从而推高了其建筑物的价值。根据租赁网站 Apartment List 的数据，2021 年至 2022 年 18 个月内，租金要价上涨了 25%。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=88CDF171-D046-4FD4-A4BB-72130DCCB4C6&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fa-real-estate-haven-turns-perilous-with-roughly-1-trillion-coming-due-74d20528&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">由于住房供应短缺，开发商正在将更多空置办公室改造成公寓。但并非所有建筑物都适合重复利用，尽管美国各地有超过 10 亿平方英尺的办公空间闲置 图片插图：Amber Bragdon<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>对于许多投资者来说，这些因素<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/rising-interest-rates-concern-apartment-building-owners-renters-11653393600?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">证明支付高价是合理的</a>。公寓楼业主通常从债券市场借入超过 80% 的建筑价值。大多数公寓贷款都是固定利率的长期抵押贷款。然而，在疫情期间，投资者获得了更多<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/bonds-backed-by-apartments-are-under-stress-as-housing-market-cools-9717d617?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">短期浮动利率贷款</a>。</p><p>许多投资者大幅提高租金，押注一旦他们的建筑物产生更高的租金收入，他们就可以以更高的估值出售建筑物或为债务再融资。</p><p>但很少有人预料到利率会上升得如此之快，从而压低建筑价值并迫使房东以更高的利率进行再融资。作为重要资金来源的地区性银行如今的放贷量大幅减少，导致抵押贷款再融资变得更加困难。美国许多城市<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/renters-are-about-to-get-the-upper-hand-f6387df4?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">的租金增长大幅放缓</a><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/renters-are-about-to-get-the-upper-hand-f6387df4?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">，</a>而通货膨胀和保险费上涨则提高了建筑物的运营成本。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><img width="600" height="800" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-830093?width=600" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p>主要由浮动利率债务和小投资者现金资助的一批新的私人房地产公司已成为多户住宅市场上更大的竞争对手。一些人基于对未来几年租金大幅上涨的乐观预期而支付了更高的价格。现在，他们在使数字发挥作用方面遇到了困难。</p><p>总部位于洛杉矶的 Tides Equities 自 2016 年以来已收购了价值超过 65 亿美元的租赁房产，其中大部分是西南部城市的中低收入公寓楼。评级机构报告显示，2021 年，该公司预计达拉斯郊区的一处房产的租金将在三年内上涨 44%。<br><br> 6 月，Tides 告诉投资者，该战略并未按计划进行。该公司在一封信中表示，租户“现金变得过于紧张”。信中称，一些房产不再赚取足够的钱来偿还债务，投资者可能需要投入更多资金来挽救建筑物免于违约。</p><p> Tides 联合创始人 Sean Kia 和 Ryan Andrade 在接受采访时表示，他们正在与贷方合作，寻找避免面临困难的房产违约的方法。</p><p>总部位于休斯敦的 Nitya Capital 拥有价值约 30 亿美元的多户住宅，该公司在 3 月份通知投资者，由于利率上升，该公司将大幅削减利润预期。</p><p> Nitya 首席执行官 Swapnil Agarwal 在一封投资者信中写道：“我们实际上是在支付更高的抵押贷款成本，而不是进行现金分配。”</p><p>公寓业主仍有理由保持乐观。即使银行撤退，<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/FNMA" class="company-name">房利美</a>和<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/FMCC" class="company-name">房地美</a>仍能提供政府支持的可靠贷款来源。大多数分析师预计住房短缺和高租金将持续存在。如果利率下降，房地产价格可能会迅速反弹。拥有固定利率抵押贷款的多户家庭业主更有能力度过任何近期的动荡。</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>您对商业地产的前景如何？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p>尽管如此，其他威胁仍在加剧。今年和明年开业的新公寓楼数量异常多，特别是在高端租赁市场，引起了供应方面的担忧。</p><p> CoStar资本市场分析全国总监查德·利特尔(Chad Littell)表示，此外，公寓楼价值比商业楼宇价值更容易受到利率上涨的影响，因为它们与10年期国债价格密切相关，而随着利率上升，十年期国债价格暴跌。</p><p>即使是一些经历过风暴的资深房地产投资者也显得很脆弱。旧金山最大的房东之一<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/NZ/XNZE/GSH" class="">Veritas Investments</a><span class="company-name-type">及其</span>合作伙伴在过去一年中拖欠了 95 栋出租建筑的债务。结果，该公司将损失超过三分之一的旧金山投资组合。</p><p>该公司今年早些时候表示，“多户型房地产行业正面临着许多与其他资产类别（包括办公楼、零售业和酒店业）相同的财务挑战。”</p><p>写信给 Konrad Putzier <a href="mailto:konrad.putzier@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">（konrad.putzier@wsj.com）</a>和 Will Parker（ <a href="mailto:will.parker@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">will.parker@wsj.com</a> ）</p><p id="correction" class="correction"><strong>更正和放大</strong><br>Blackstone 的 11 栋曼哈顿公寓楼组合正在进行特殊维修。这个故事的先前版本错误地表示他们默认了。 （8月7日更正）</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 09:30:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/a-real-estate-haven-turns-perilous-with-roughly-1-trillion-coming-due-74d20528</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/a-real-estate-haven-turns-perilous-with-roughly-1-trillion-coming-due-74d20528<author><![CDATA[Konrad PutzierWill Parker]]></author><category>住房</category><category>商业地产</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>住房</category><category>商业房地产</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>黑色的石头</category><category>巴克斯</category><category>房利美</category><category>国家气象局</category><category>房地美</category><category>FMCC</category><category>科星集团</category><category>CSGP</category><category>良好的精神好客</category><category>谷胱甘肽新西兰</category><category>新西兰：还原型谷胱甘肽</category><category>彼得·索托洛夫</category><category>肖恩·基亚</category><category>瑞安·安德拉德</category><category>斯瓦普尼尔·阿加瓦尔</category><category>查德·利特尔</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Anansi’s Gold’ Review: Treasure Map to Nowhere]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>他知道如何找到加纳领导人向国外汇出的数十亿美元，但首先他需要投资者来让他（奢侈地）维持生计。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB12770427345856314244904590122110697799470"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-830546?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">约翰·布莱-米扎。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Yepoka Yeebo </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB12770427345856314244904590122110697799470"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">弗兰克·<span class="author" itemprop="name">甘农</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 6 日下午 4:58 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/anansis-gold-review-treasure-map-to-nowhere-a3990d04"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> 20 世纪 70 年代中期，一位名叫约翰·布莱-米扎 (John Blay-Miezah) 的富有魅力的加纳年轻人在伦敦、纽约和费城闲逛。这位彬彬有礼的宾夕法尼亚大学毕业生，现年 30 岁出头，有一个惊人的故事要讲，也有一笔非凡的交易。</p><p>他向所有愿意倾听的人讲述了 1972 年 4 月，他在布加勒斯特陪伴加纳首任总统夸梅·恩克鲁玛临终的情景。在生命的最后时刻，这位流亡领袖向他的部落兄弟和门生吐露了这个传闻已久的故事是真的：在 1966 年被政变推翻之前，他成功盗取了数十亿美元的钻石、现金，尤其是 30,000 美元。从加纳到瑞士银行的金条。这笔钱专门用于他深爱的国家的改善项目，并将留在国外，直到某个更稳定的时刻可以安全地遣返。只有布莱-米扎知道账号、密码以及访问宝藏所需的程序。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
        "><div class="media-object-rich-text"><p><strong>阿纳西的黄金</strong></p><p><em>作者：叶波卡·伊博</em></p><p><em>（布卢姆斯伯里，378 页，29.99 美元）</em> </p></div></div><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/schemas/e84b6b53-c858-469a-9713-9d8c94f25e4e.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p>布莱-米扎告诉听众，他现在已准备好执行恩克鲁玛的指示，并且他相信只需要几周甚至最多几个月就能拿到这笔钱。与此同时，他正在寻找人来支付他的开支。他并不指望美德本身会得到回报，因为除了帮助一个陷入困境的非洲国家的满足感之外，投资者还可以保证获得惊人的回报：每投资一美元，回报率为 10 比 1、20 比 1，甚至 100 比 1。支持者和投资者并不难找到——从贫穷的寡妇到前美国司法部长约翰·米切尔（1979 年出狱后的他）。钱就涌进来了。</p><p>但布莱-米扎的故事存在问题。首先，他最接近在宾夕法尼亚大学学习的经历是在费城联合联盟俱乐部当服务员。他没有在罗马尼亚恩克鲁玛的临终病床上，而是在费城郊外一个小时的格拉特福德州立惩教所因欺诈罪而服刑。</p><p>首次入读英国裔加纳作家耶波卡·伊博 (Yepoka Yeebo) 在《安纳西的黄金：掠夺西方、智胜华盛顿、欺骗世界的人》一书中，以辛辣的沉着讲述了布莱-米扎的夸张生活和任性的职业生涯。伊博女士认出布莱-米扎就是神秘的加纳骗子阿南西。就像中国的孙悟空一样，阿南西用他的诡计来欺骗和欺骗更大、更强的人。虽然《阿纳西的黄金》反映了大量令人畏惧的研究，但它读起来就像一本流浪汉小说。</p><p>据 Yeebo 女士记载，近二十年来，Blay-Miezah 一直通过揭露阻碍他获得资金的令人讨厌的新技术来拉拢投资者。很快，一种模式就出现了。经过无休止的拖延后，投资者将被召集到加纳（或瑞士或开曼群岛），期待已久的付款终于在那里发生。几天后，布莱-米扎就会消失。最终他会在其他地方重新出现，循环又会开始。</p><p>伊博女士指出，美国驻加纳大使秀兰·邓波儿·布莱克（Shirley Temple Black）看穿了布莱-米扎并试图警告其他人。在 1975 年给国务卿亨利·基辛格的一封电报中，她解释了这个问题：“那些认为布莱-米扎是骗子的人担心他可能只是有钱，然后他们就会显得极其愚蠢。”</p><p>布莱-米扎是个大人物，生活也很大。他的定制西装、镶满珠宝的手指、时尚的豪华轿车、私人厨师和顶层套房增加了他的神秘感，而不是削弱了他的可信度。他对投资者（以及他的妻子，她因追踪他的调情的巧妙方法而被昵称为“科伦坡”）不忠诚，但他始终忠于自己内心的骗子。适时地制造健康恐慌是他的惯用伎俩。伊博女士描述了他在一家医院里的情况，监视器发出蜂鸣声，脸上戴着氧气面罩：“布莱-米扎睁开眼睛迎接来访者。一位投资者向他提供了一叠现金。他一动不动，除了右手慢慢地从床单下面伸出来，抓住现金，然后又消失在床单下面。”</p><p> 1979 年，布莱-米扎找到了一种逃避起诉并获得大量资源的方法：他将成为加纳总统。他不受事实束缚，不受现实约束，以反腐败候选人的身份参选。当他看起来确实有机会获胜时，政府以贿赂、伪证和伪造罪名起诉他。为了确定起见，他的名字已从选票中删除。</p><p>对于一个较轻的骗子来说，有罪判决和九年监禁将是终结。但前方仍然有许多擦伤和逃跑。最终，是埃德·布拉德利和《60 分钟》击败了布莱-米扎。该片段于 1989 年 1 月播出，标题为“终极骗子”。布莱-米扎本人可能是迷人且令人信服的。在电视上，他被认为是虚伪且荒谬的。三年后，他因心脏病发作而去世——或者正如伊博女士所说，他可能没有去世。不管怎样，葬礼还是举行了，1993 年，一个长得很像他的人被埋葬在阿克拉。</p><p>虽然伊博女士的叙述引人入胜，但她的一些后殖民分析却值得商榷。她忽略了过高利润的明显动机，写道布莱-米扎的黑人投资者希望“修复殖民主义的创伤”，而他的白人投资者则看到了“掠夺非洲国家祖传财富”的机会。</p><p>反常的是，布莱-米扎骗局的力量和恩克鲁玛黄金的诱惑依然存在。 2009 年，加纳政府的一个官方委员会没有发现任何证据表明黄金曾经存在过。但贪婪是永恒的，伊博女士指出，“现在，在世界的某个地方，有人正在撒布莱-米扎关于恩克鲁玛黄金的谎言，有人正在投资它。”</p><p><em>甘农先生是尼克松白宫的总统特别助理。</em></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 06 Aug 2023 20:58:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/anansis-gold-review-treasure-map-to-nowhere-a3990d04</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/anansis-gold-review-treasure-map-to-nowhere-a3990d04<category>图书</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>艺术/娱乐</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 排除过滤器</category><category>评论</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>观点</category><category>图书</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>艺术</category><category>娱乐</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>c&amp;e 排除过滤器</category><category>评论</category><category>观点</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Arts Calendar: Happenings for the Week of August 6]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>德古拉在海上恐吓一艘船，一部深入探讨《大白鲨》制作过程的戏剧，《大楼谋杀案》以新一季回归等等。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJO-0000022923"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-830181?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">乌佐·阿杜巴和马修·布罗德里克在《止痛药》中</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Netflix</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJO-0000022923"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> 《华尔街日报》艺术评论人员</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 6 日上午 5:00 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/arts-calendar-happenings-for-the-week-of-august-6-airdigital-9bd1d86"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><h3>电影</h3><p><strong>•</strong> <strong>“德墨忒尔的最后一次航行”</strong> <em>（8 月 11 日）</em> ：如果水手们认为坏血病是他们在海上面临的最可怕的威胁，那么他们就错了——至少如果他们让德古拉作为不受欢迎的偷渡者登上了船上的话。安德烈·奥夫雷达尔（《无名氏尸检》）的这部新片改编自布拉姆·斯托克的经典恐怖小说中的一个章节，由科里·霍金斯、艾斯林·弗朗西奥西、利亚姆·坎宁安、大卫·达斯马齐安和哈维尔·博泰特主演，讲述了一个令人难忘的航海故事。</p><p> <strong>•</strong> <strong>“朱尔斯”</strong> <em>（8 月 11 日）</em> ：一位老人在宾夕法尼亚州的一个小镇上享受着安静而又无聊的生活，直到一个不明飞行物坠入他的后院。本·金斯利 (Ben Kingsley) 在马克·特特托布 (Marc Turtletaub) 的最新作品中扮演受惊的主角。</p><p> <strong>•</strong> <strong>“Medusa Deluxe”</strong> <em>（8 月 11 日）</em> ：当一名美发比赛的参赛者死亡时，分叉的头发成为了这场谋杀之谜中参赛者最不担心的事情。托马斯·哈迪曼首次执导长片，主演包括克莱尔·帕金斯、凯·亚历山大、达雷尔·德席尔瓦和卢克·帕斯夸里诺。</p><p> <strong>•</strong> <strong>《奥罗拉的日出》</strong> <em>（8 月 11 日）</em> ：Inna Sahakyan 的动画纪录片，亚美尼亚角逐 2023 年奥斯卡奖，讲述了亚美尼亚种族灭绝幸存者奥罗拉·马尔迪加尼安 (Aurora Mardiganian) 的故事，她被送上死亡行军，被卖为奴隶，最终逃脱并前往纽约。在那里，她成为一名演员和作家，在 1919 年一部讲述暴行的无声电影中扮演自己。</p><p> <strong>•</strong> <strong>“两个世界之间”</strong> <em>（8 月 11 日）</em> ：正如弗洛伦斯·奥伯纳斯（Florence Aubenas）备受赞誉的著作《夜间清洁工》中所描述的那样，这位记者以非技术工人的身份卧底，并在经济衰退期间找到了不稳定的工作。现在，伊曼纽尔·卡雷尔（Emmanuel Carrère）（《对手》）执导的一部法国戏剧取材于该作品，朱丽叶·比诺什（Juliette Binoche）饰演一名由记者转型为看门人的角色。</p><p> <strong>•</strong> <strong>《永恒的记忆》</strong> <em>（8 月 11 日）</em> ：这部由 Maite Alberdi（其作品《鼹鼠特工》获得奥斯卡最佳纪录片提名）制作的纪录片荣获圣丹斯电影节评审团大奖，讲述了智利记者 Augusto Góngora 与女演员宝琳娜·乌鲁蒂亚 (Paulina Urrutia) 与奥古斯托 (Augusto) 的老年痴呆症进一步恶化，两人在一起已有二十多年，宝琳娜 (Paulina Urrutia) 一直在照顾他。</p><p> <strong>•</strong> <strong>“煤炭之王”</strong> <em>（8 月 11 日）</em> ：无论从字面上还是比喻上来说，煤炭都是一个热门话题，它以其他话题无法比拟的方式触及美国的文化、经济、生活和政治。纪录片导演伊莱恩·麦克米利恩·谢尔顿通过现代阿巴拉契亚矿工女儿的故事来审视煤炭在我们共同历史中的地位。</p><p> <strong>•</strong> <strong>“Love Life”</strong> <em>（8 月 11 日）</em> ：深田浩司的戏剧在电影节巡回演出中赢得好评后，登陆美国影院。当妻子儿子的父亲以悲惨的方式出现在一对幸福的日本夫妇的生活中时，他们的生活被颠覆了。</p><p> <strong>•</strong> <strong>“Pod 一代”</strong> <em><strong>&nbsp;</strong> （8 月 11 日）</em> ：为分娩做准备需要准备很多<em>东西</em>：书籍、婴儿床、衣服、人造机器人子宫。最后一个可能还没有出现在婴儿登记处，但在苏菲·巴特的科幻浪漫喜剧中的未来纽约，它是怀孕过程的标准。艾米莉亚·克拉克 (Emilia Clarke) 和切瓦特·埃加福特 (Chiwetel Ejiofor) 饰演故事中心的一对热爱科技的父母。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-830173?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">哈维尔·博泰特和科里·霍金斯在《德墨忒尔号的最后一次航行》中</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：环球影业和 Amblin Entertainment</p></figcaption></figure></div><h3>电视</h3><p><strong>•</strong> <strong>“胜利时刻：湖人王朝的崛起”第 2 季</strong><em>（HBO，8 月 6 日）</em> ：亚当·麦凯 (Adam McKay) 制作的电视剧，讲述了看似势不可挡的 80 年代湖人队的崛起——参见：卡里姆·阿卜杜勒·贾巴尔 (Kareem Abdul-Jabbar)、魔术师约翰逊 (Magic Johnson)、迈克尔 (Michael)库珀,</p>等人——在 1980 年 NBA 总冠军之后又回来了。<p></p><p> <strong>•</strong> <strong>“Hard Knocks”</strong> <em>（HBO，8 月 8 日）</em> ：从 Showtime 时代到摇摇欲坠的特许经营权，HBO 很乐意讲述各个领域的体育故事。这部长期播出的 NFL 纪录片系列的最新一期，讲述了纽约喷气机队的幕后故事——该队第二次出现在节目中——他们希望在新交易（但年事已高）的亚伦·罗杰斯的带领下，在去年 7-10 赛季的基础上取得进步。中心。</p><p> <strong>•</strong> <strong>《大楼里的谋杀案》第三季</strong><em>（Hulu，8 月 8 日）</em> ：保罗·路德 (Paul Rudd) 加入这部热门喜剧/悬疑剧的演员阵容，在马丁·肖特 (Martin Short) 所饰演的角色执导的戏剧中担任演员。其他演员阵容包括阿什利·帕克、梅丽尔·斯特里普和杰西·威廉姆斯，而史蒂夫·马丁、赛琳娜·戈麦斯和其他熟悉的面孔也在回归的演员之列。</p><p> <strong>•</strong> <strong>《奇异星球》</strong> <em>（Apple TV+，8 月 9 日）</em> ：在《瑞克与莫蒂》联合创作者丹·哈蒙 (Dan Harmon) 的帮助下，内森·W·派尔 (Nathan W. Pyle) 对他的网络漫画进行了电视处理，该漫画讲述了蓝色外星人对外星人的活动感到惊讶的故事。 Earth-bound would find quotidian. TV on the Radio frontman Tunde Adebimpe joins Danny Pudi (“Community”) and Lori Tan Chinn in voicing the easily amused extraterrestrials.</p><p> <strong>•</strong> <strong>“Painkiller”</strong> <em>(Netflix, Aug. 10)</em> : Peter Berg (“Friday Night Lights”) directs this six-part drama, based on the book of the same name by Barry Meier and Patrick Radden Keefe&#39;s New Yorker story about the Sackler family, that tells the saga of America&#39;s opiate-addiction crisis. Uzo Aduba, Matthew Broderick, Sam Anderson and</p> Taylor Kitsch are among the cast.<p></p><p> <strong>•</strong> <strong>“Heart of Stone”</strong> <em>(Netflix, Aug. 11)</em> : Gal Gadot hangs up her golden lasso for a moment to embark on a different kind of adventure, this one more covert than her gig as Wonder Woman. An international agent with the usual deadly and dexterous résumé, her Rachel Stone is tasked with making sure a secret weapon doesn&#39;t fall into the wrong hands. Jamie Dornan co-stars in the film directed by “Peaky Blinders” alum Tom Harper.</p><p> <strong>•</strong> <strong>“Red, White &amp; Royal Blue”</strong> <em>(Prime Video, Aug. 11)</em> : The enemies-become-lovers setup gets an international-relations twist when the son of the US president and the Prince of Wales are thrown together to make nice after a public spat only to discover a new side to the transatlantic “special relationship.” Based on Casey McQuiston&#39;s bestseller and directed by Matthew López (the Tony-winning writer of “The Inheritance”), the film stars Taylor Zakhar Perez, Nicholas Galitzine, Uma Thurman and Stephen Fry.</p><h3> Theater</h3><p> <strong>•</strong> <strong>“The Shark Is Broken”</strong> <em>(John Golden Theatre, New York, opens Aug. 10)</em> : We&#39;re gonna need a bigger boat—or at least a prop that works. After successful runs at the Edinburgh Fringe and in London, this comedy dives into the making of “Jaws” and the technical—and personal—difficulties that had to be overcome to create the summer classic.</p><h3> Music</h3><p> <strong>•</strong> <strong>Lincoln Center Celebrates the 50th Anniversary of Hip-Hop</strong> <em>(Various Locations, New York, Aug. 9-12)</em> : We live in a world that&#39;s impossible to imagine without hip-hop, so wide has its influence been—not just on music, but art, fashion, film, sports and beyond. But there was a time, not all that long ago, when it was far from ubiquitous. Born in the Bronx in the summer of &#39;73, the movement now celebrates its Golden Jubilee and Lincoln Center is throwing it a party—or rather a series of parties. Dancing, musical performances, improvisation and other events pop up across the city in this series whose participants include Arthur Verocai, Rakim and more.</p><p> <strong>•</strong> <strong>Johnathan Blake, “Passage”</strong> <em>(Aug. 11)</em> : The second Blue Note album from the jazz drummer, composer and bandleader is a labor of love dedicated to and honoring his late father. It again features his electrifying group, Pentad, which comprises Immanuel Wilkins on alto saxophone, Joel Ross on vibraphone, David Virelles on piano and Dezron Douglas on bass.</p><p> <strong>•</strong> <strong>Bonnie “Prince” Billy, “Keeping Secrets Will Destroy You”</strong> <em>(Aug. 11)</em> : The singer-songwriter Will Oldham, who now performs as Bonnie “Prince” Billy, returns with the latest addition to his very deep catalog, a record that finds the 53-year-old operating in a slightly lower register than before while still experimenting with sound and lyrics in the way that has earned him a loyal following.</p><p> <strong>•</strong> <strong>Neil Young, “Chrome Dreams”</strong> <em><strong>&nbsp;</strong> (Aug. 11)</em> : True Neil Young fans might have already heard a version of his latest record—his 44th. Compiled in 1977 but never released, a bootleg version has been circulating for decades. Now fans of the folk-country mainstay will be able to get their hands on an authorized version.</p><h3> Art</h3><p> <strong>•</strong> <strong>“James Brooks: A Painting Is a Real Thing”</strong> <em>(Parrish Art Museum, Water Mill, NY, Aug. 6–Oct. 15)</em> :  The first major retrospective in 35 years of the artist who dedicated himself to painting throughout his career, this show contains over 100 objects, revealing the stunning breadth of styles Brooks embraced in his practice, from experiments in Abstract Expressionism to impressionism-influenced vistas to realist draftsmanship.</p><p> <strong>•</strong> <strong>“Jammie Holmes: Make the Revolution Irresistible”</strong> <em>(Modern Art Museum of Fort Worth, Texas, Aug. 11–Nov. 26)</em> : The first solo museum show of the contemporary realist&#39;s works, this exhibition explores the Dallas-based artist&#39;s treatments of race, masculinity and mourning with a particular eye to the context of the American South. With some 15 paintings spanning his career, MAMFW examines how the Louisiana-born Holmes has grappled with his place—socially, culturally, artistically—within the region and how art can be used as a vehicle for both self-affirmation and vulnerability.</p><p> <strong>•</strong> <strong>“Jegi: Korean Ritual Objects”</strong> <em>(The Met Fifth Avenue, New York, Aug. 6-Oct. 15)</em> : Ritual continues to play an important role across our lives—birthdays, weddings, funerals—and it was no different during Korea&#39;s lengthy Joseon dynasty (1392-1910), with rituals we&#39;re intimately familiar with today in the West, as well as more culturally unique celebrations: remembrances of deceased ancestors many generations on, the Lunar New Year, Chuseok (the Harvest Moon Festival). A show at the Met highlights the items that held offerings of food and drink, as well as accessories that have been an integral part of these ceremonies across the centuries.</p><p> <strong>•</strong> <strong>“LA Art Book Fair”</strong> <em>(The Geffen Contemporary at MOCA, Los Angeles, Aug. 10-13)</em> : Now 10 years old, Printed Matter&#39;s LA Art Book Fair—the first since 2019, after a lengthy Covid-imposed hiatus—features publishers ranging from the hyper-indie to the institutional who offer the most engaging artists&#39; books on the market along with a series of book releases, talks, performances and more.</p><h3> Last Call</h3><p> <strong>•</strong> <strong>“Georgia O&#39;Keeffe: To See Takes Time”</strong> <em>(Museum of Modern Art, New York, through Aug. 12)</em> : This exhibition of some 120 works on paper, made in series, explores O&#39;Keeffe&#39;s creative process and crafts an argument for her as an intimate abstractionist. The museum&#39;s first solo show dedicated to her in decades, it reveals how, in the <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/georgia-okeeffe-beyond-the-canvas-fa0258cd?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">words of our critic</a> , “at her best, O&#39;Keeffe distills the world into essences.”</p><p> <strong>•</strong> <strong>“Jaune Quick-to-See Smith: Memory Map”</strong> <em>(Whitney Museum, New York, through Aug. 13)</em> : Ms. Smith, a member of the Confederated Salish and Kootenai Tribes, receives her first New York retrospective. Collecting drawings, prints, paintings and sculptures by the 83-year-old, the exhibition reveals her far-flung art-historical influences, from Pop to neo-expressionism, filtered through her unique perspectives as a Native American artist.</p><p> For additional Arts Calendar listings visit wsj.com. Write to brian.kelly@wsj.com and julia.fischer@wsj.com.</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 06 Aug 2023 09:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/arts-calendar-happenings-for-the-week-of-august-6-airdigital-9bd1d86</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/arts-calendar-happenings-for-the-week-of-august-6-airdigital-9bd1d86<category> arts in review</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>名人</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>艺术/娱乐</category><category>生活/生活方式</category><category>Movies</category><category>凶杀案</category><category>Calendar of Events</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 排除过滤器</category><category>IWE过滤器</category><category>日常新闻</category><category>Arts in Review</category><category> SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>名人</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>艺术</category><category>娱乐</category><category>活的</category><category>生活方式</category><category>movies</category><category>凶杀案</category><category>calendar of events</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>c&amp;e 排除过滤器</category><category>伊威过滤器</category><category>常规新闻</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Give Me a Sign: The Language of Symbols’ Review: Pictures Worth a Thousand Words]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> At Cooper Hewitt, Smithsonian Design Museum, an exhibition examines the legacy of designer Henry Dreyfuss and the fascinating histories behind many of the everyday symbols that connect people throughout the world. <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB12070190061687823722304590122083353985598"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-829926?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Henry Dreyfuss drawing a symbol</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Cooper Hewitt, Smithsonian Design Museum </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB12070190061687823722304590122083353985598"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/edward-rothstein" itemprop="url" rel="author">Edward Rothstein</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Aug. 5, 2023 7:00 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/give-me-a-sign-the-language-of-symbols-review-cooper-hewitt-smithsonian-design-museum-henry-dreyfuss-35a6e120"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p><em>纽约</em></p><p>At the very beginning of the “Symbol Sourcebook: An Authoritative Guide to International Graphic Symbols” (1972), the book&#39;s author and one of the era&#39;s most accomplished industrial designers, Henry Dreyfuss (1904-1972), presents the same word in Greek, in Japanese, in Russian and in Hebrew. None can be read or understood if you are only at home with the Roman alphabet. Even if you could get a translation, the words themselves hardly seem to suggest matters of life and death. But a single symbol instantly crosses cultural and linguistic boundaries, commanding attention: a skull and crossbones. In a word, “poison.” </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4></h4><p> <strong>Give Me A Sign: The Language of Symbols</strong></p><p> <em>Cooper Hewitt, Smithsonian Design Museum, through Sept. 2, 2024</em></p></div></div><p> Such is the power of symbols. And if you open the Dreyfuss book, which is still in active use a half-century after compilation, or if you turn the digital pages on a touch screen at Cooper Hewitt, Smithsonian Design Museum in “Give Me a Sign: The Language of Symbols”—an exhibition devoted to the Sourcebook, its creator, and its legacy—you will see dozens of icons with meanings as compelling as that death&#39;s head.</p><p> Dreyfuss&#39;s ambition was to create an international language of signs that could accomplish what artificial world languages like Esperanto could not. The Table of Contents appears in 18 languages. The symbols are distilled from a database of 20,000 icons. They are organized into 26 disciplines and categories. And even after a half-century, most retain their power. I doubt if there is much use today for an icon associated with whirring computer tape drives meaning “Magnetic Tape Unit Occupied” (looking a bit like an empty film reel), but is there a driver who does not understand the sign/label for “windshield wiper” (a curved two-dimensional arc with a tilted, off-center line extending through it)? To a great extent we are still living in Dreyfuss&#39;s world. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="522" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-829873?width=700&amp;height=522" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Poster for the &#39;Symbol Sourcebook&#39;</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Cooper Hewitt, Smithsonian Design Museum</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> The exhibition, organized by Emily M. Orr, associate curator at Cooper Hewitt, draws on the Henry Dreyfuss Archive, housed at the museum; it is being publicly explored for the first time. We begin by surveying Dreyfuss&#39;s ideas about symbols, including their ability to be combined to create new meanings, the way, say, a red circle with a diagonal slash (signifying prohibition) can be placed over a car silhouette: automobiles forbidden! We also see three icons Dreyfuss successfully used on the outside of a package shipped from Moscow that have become standard: An open umbrella? Keep dry. A broken goblet? Fragile. Two up arrows? Keep upright.</p><p> But many of these were not invented by Dreyfuss. He used what the exhibition describes as an early form of crowdsourcing, sending out questionnaires, internationally soliciting thousands of designs. Submissions were modified and codified.</p><p> Dreyfuss also created a symbol for the entire project, which the exhibition describes as a “human figure framed by a triangle, circle, and square.” It deliberately looks like a rough sketch—a work in progress. And unlike Leonardo da Vinci&#39;s idealized Vitruvian Man, in which the male figure is perfectly inscribed in a circle and square, here the abstract geometric forms are freeform. The human simply stands in the center—which is one of Dreyfuss&#39;s principles. As we see here, when he undertook a redesign of John Deere tractors in 1969, he paid particular attention to the human “interface” and how the machine would be used; controls were given distinctive shapes and textures so they could be distinguished by touch alone.</p><p> Dreyfuss&#39;s design career could have played an even bigger role here. He created products that often deserved the overused description “iconic.” He and his firm are credited with many of the major telephone designs offered by Bell Telephone Laboratories, shaping the look of the instrument for a generation. His circular Honeywell thermostats established a standard that still resonates. He designed airplane interiors, alarm clocks and vacuum cleaners. And devised symbols that would make their use easier.</p><p> But as Dreyfuss knew, symbols are not timeless representations. The Sourcebook shows transformations in images of Olympic sports between the London Games of 1948 and the Munich Games of 1972, inspiring one gallery here. In 1948, we see, line drawings of sports equipment took representational pride of place—boxing gloves, a sailboat, crossed fencing swords; but in 1972, schematic human figures proliferated, always represented in motion, prepared to lunge or dive or row. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="493" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-829870?width=700&amp;height=493" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Poster for the 1972 Munich Olympics</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Cooper Hewitt, Smithsonian Design Museum</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Even more revealing is the exhibition&#39;s discussion of the familiar “Accessible Icon” that evolved from a design by a Danish student in 1968; it shows a stick figure erect in a static wheelchair, “as though waiting to be pushed to a destination.” It was adopted by at least 25 countries by 1972 and appears in the Sourcebook. But just over decade ago, there was a “community-based effort” to redesign it as “an empowering image”: The figure is thickened and leans forward as if in motion, arms poised above the wheels.</p><p> The exhibition does not sufficiently discuss the proliferation of symbols in recent decades on computer and phone screens—thus missing an opportunity to show how new technologies might deliberately invoke antiquated symbols, the way Apple&#39;s operating systems use a mechanical gear for their settings app. And the show&#39;s extended attention to the creation of hijab-wearing emojis and to the activist symbol of the raised fist are not particularly compelling.</p><p> But in one display, the show challenges visitors to design effective symbols from elements provided, and such challenges lead visitors to explore and inquire further. What makes for a truly awful symbol, like those on our clothes&#39; washing labels? And why, as Dreyfuss himself asked, are there no satisfactory symbols for “push” and “pull”? Symbolically speaking, the show thus leaves us with a healthy number of question marks, accompanying a considerable number of exclamation points.</p><p class="articleTagLine"> —Mr. Rothstein is the Journal&#39;s Critic-at-Large.</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 11:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/give-me-a-sign-the-language-of-symbols-review-cooper-hewitt-smithsonian-design-museum-henry-dreyfuss-35a6e120</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/give-me-a-sign-the-language-of-symbols-review-cooper-hewitt-smithsonian-design-museum-henry-dreyfuss-35a6e120<author><![CDATA[Edward Rothstein]]></author><category> arts in review</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>艺术/娱乐</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 排除过滤器</category><category>Reviews</category><category> Arts in Review</category><category> SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>艺术</category><category>娱乐</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>c&amp;e 排除过滤器</category><category>reviews </category></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Bark Out Thunder Roar Out Lightning’ and ‘Lowcountry’ Reviews: Southern Stories Renewed Through Jazz]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Trumpeter Chief Adjuah, formerly known as Christian Scott, sets aside his usual instrument and embraces his Black Indian heritage on a new album; Lowcountry&#39;s self-titled record combines modern jazz with the musical traditions of Gullah culture. <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11490979256760064080404590116052446285656"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="1290" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-829927?width=860&amp;height=1290" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Chief Xian aTunde Adjuah</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Ropeadope Records </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11490979256760064080404590116052446285656"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name">Larry Blumenfeld</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Aug. 5, 2023 7:00 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/bark-out-thunder-roar-out-lightning-and-lowcountry-reviews-southern-stories-renewed-through-jazz-883d20d"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> In the American South, music recovers histories, especially of African-American traditions, and sometimes reinvents them. Two new releases (both on Ropeadope)— <strong>“Bark Out Thunder Roar Out Lightning,”</strong> from Chief Adjuah (formerly Christian Scott ); and <strong>“Lowcountry,”</strong> by a collective with that name—reflect this truth with force and beauty.</p><p> Christian Scott grew up in the Upper Ninth Ward of New Orleans. His grandfather, Donald Harrison Sr. , was a Big Chief of Black Indian culture, in which ancestral history, personal independence and community cohesion are expressed through chants and declarations, along with hand-drummed rhythms and elaborate feathered-and-beaded suits. His uncle, Donald Harrison Jr. , best known as an alto saxophonist and a standard-bearer of modern jazz, is also a Big Chief.</p><p> Before Mr. Adjuah picked up the trumpet with which, as Christian Scott, he has earned widespread acclaim, he was immersed in this familial tradition. (He became a chief himself in 2017.) On his new release, as Chief Adjuah (drawn from his full adopted legal name, Xian aTunde Adjuah ), he plays no trumpet at all. On “Blood Calls Blood,” he opens the album strumming “Chief Adjuah&#39;s Bow,” a 20-string electric instrument that blends elements of two West African instruments, the <em>n&#39;goni</em> and <em>kora</em> , with those of a European harp. Ninety seconds in, he sings, for the first time on record: “Listen in the wind have you learned to hear / The voices callin&#39; to you from yesteryear.”</p><p> Mr. Adjuah mines a tradition built on rhythms and vocals. Here, eight drummers and percussionists—whose instruments include a standard trap set, a “pan-African kit” and more than a dozen kinds of hand drums—represent various connected musical cultures: Joe Dyson Jr. , a New Orleans native, is a rising jazz star; Weedie Braimah, born in Ghana, is a master of the West African <em>djembe</em> . Mr. Adjuah sings on all but one track.</p><p> Honoring one&#39;s lineage is also a central aspect of this culture. “Shallow Water,” an anthem of Black Indian culture, was popularized by Mr. Adjuah&#39;s grandfather; his own lyrics to “Ashé Chief Donald” celebrate his uncle&#39;s achievements. His version of the oft-recorded R&amp;B song “ Iko Iko ” (here, titled “Xodokan Iko— Hu Na Ney ”) hews close to how it is sung in street processions, rich with overlapping calls-and-responses and organic shifts of meter.</p><p> Mr. Adjuah&#39;s original compositions are hypnotic—dreamy on “End Simulation,” and with an air of menace on “Trouble That Mornin&#39;.” The 15-minute-plus title track forms the album&#39;s emotional core. Here, his custom-made bow sounds as percussive as Mr. Braimah&#39;s drums, his singing proud yet pained, and his lyrics pointed: “I think you can&#39;t outrun those fires born of the violence.”</p><p> Black Indian tradition has had notable crossover moments: In the 1970s, albums by Bo Dollis&#39;s Wild Magnolias and the Wild Tchoupitoulas made it visionary funk; Donald Harrison Jr.&#39;s 1992 release, “Indian Blues,” distilled it into jazz. Mr. Adjuah broadens this reach, and makes a mesmerizing personal statement about entwined histories of African empires, Native American nations, New Orleans forebears, and his own life and times.</p><h4> *** </h4><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-829973?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Members of the Gullah-influenced jazz ensemble Lowcountry</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Ropeadope Records</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Trumpeter Matt White, who is chair of jazz studies at the University of South Carolina, knew little about Gullah culture when, a decade ago, he made field recordings of elders on St. Helena Island. Entranced by the traditional songs of the Gullah people—descendants of enslaved West Africans in the Lowcountry regions and Sea Islands of the Deep South. He kept returning.</p><p> Gullah songs have long influenced American music—from George Gershwin&#39;s opera “Porgy and Bess” to the Grammy-winning band Ranky Tanky. Mr. White aims both to preserve Gullah songs and to reimagine them. The Lowcountry collective he assembled is anchored by Quentin Baxter,</p> Ranky Tanky&#39;s drummer, who deftly blends the Gullah beats of his upbringing in Charleston, SC, with modern-jazz mastery.<p></p><p> These tracks are set in motion by Gracie Gadsen and Joseph and Rosa Murray, who are husband and wife. They are all “song leaders” in Gullah tradition, who “line and raise” melodies learned from elders, mostly at Praise House services. Mr. White recorded them narrating cultural histories and singing Gullah songs in their homes. He then crafted arrangements, for which he gathered jazz musicians and, on six tracks, the Charleston Symphony String Quartet, in a recording studio. He wove these elements together, often to seamless effect. On four tracks, the celebrated tenor saxophonist Chris Potter, who grew up in Columbia, SC, becomes another sort of song leader, his improvisations forming the calls for other musicians&#39; responses.</p><p> On “ Aye Neva, ” an old “shouting song,” Mr. Murray sings the Gullah phrase “day come clean” (signaling the start of the day), repeating it like a chant. Mr. Potter turns the notes and cadence into a melodic cell. As embellished by the jazz ensemble and string players—13 musicians in all—the harmonies change hues, not unlike a sunrise. Soon, Mr. Baxter syncopates bass-drum kicks with beats of his tambourine, an instrument he first played as a boy in church.</p><p> Before any of this music, Gullah musician and cultural preservationist Ron Daise</p> recites an original poem, “Forgotten Moments”: “A history of a people has been hushed,” he says. “Progress and short-sightedness are silencing a heritage.” To end the album, “Come By Here,” the Gullah traditional best known as “Kumbaya,” becomes a ballad, highlighted by Mr. White&#39;s sweet-toned fluegelhorn set against pizzicato strings.<p></p><p> With reverence and unhushed abandon, Chief Adjuah and Lowcountry extend legacies that, however threatened or overlooked, are still very much alive.</p><p class="articleTagLine"> —Mr. Blumenfeld writes about jazz and Afro-Latin music for the Journal.</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 11:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/bark-out-thunder-roar-out-lightning-and-lowcountry-reviews-southern-stories-renewed-through-jazz-883d20d</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/bark-out-thunder-roar-out-lightning-and-lowcountry-reviews-southern-stories-renewed-through-jazz-883d20d<category> arts in review</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>艺术/娱乐</category><category>Music</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 排除过滤器</category><category>Reviews</category><category> Arts in Review</category><category> SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>艺术</category><category>娱乐</category><category>music</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>c&amp;e 排除过滤器</category><category>reviews </category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Eternal Truths Cast in Bronze: Rodin’s ‘The Gates of Hell’]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Auguste Rodin&#39;s unfinished project is the keystone to his legacy as the father of modern sculpture and an arresting portrait of humanity. <figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-827733" alt="Auguste Rodin, 'The Gates of Hell' (cast 1926-28)" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption> Auguste Rodin, &#39;The Gates of Hell&#39; (cast 1926-28) Philadelphia Museum of Art <span>Philadelphia Museum of Art</span> </figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB12070190061687823722304590126303181863836"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB12070190061687823722304590126303181863836"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name">Julia Fischer</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Aug. 4, 2023 5:45 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/eternal-truths-cast-in-bronze-rodins-the-gates-of-hell-5ea6f0bb"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p> Throughout his career, Auguste Rodin (1840-1917) looked failure in the eye. Born into a poor family, Rodin applied to the École des Beaux-Arts—an essential stepping stone for aspiring artists in France in those days—three times and was rejected over and over. So he had to make his way on his own. His sculptures were often met with ridicule and rejection. Only in his late 30s did the Parisian&#39;s work spark genuine interest—both positive and negative. His breakthrough sculpture, “The Age of Bronze” (1875), a full-scale standing male nude, was so lifelike that critics accused Rodin of making a cast directly from the model.</p><p> “The Gates of Hell,” widely considered Rodin&#39;s greatest work, also might be deemed a failure. In 1880, Rodin received a commission for a pair of doors featuring reliefs illustrating Dante&#39;s “Divine Comedy,” intended for a new museum of decorative arts in Paris. The museum was never built, but Rodin kept working on “The Gates” until his death—nearly half his life—at which point they remained unfinished. The original plaster model resides at the Musée d&#39;Orsay, but after 1917 several bronze casts were made and can be seen in museums around the world. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="media-object-slideshow"><div class="strap-container"><h3 class="wsj-slideshow-title strap"> <a href="">&#39;The Gates of Hell&#39; (1880-1917) by Auguste Rodin</a></h3><h4 class="wsj-media-dek sub-strap"> Eternal Truths Cast in Bronze </h4></div><div class="wsj-slideshow-wrap"><amp-carousel layout="responsive" height="400" width="600" type="slides" controls=""><div class="slide media-object-slideshow-slide" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><img width="undefined" height="undefined" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-829113/?width=600&amp;height=400" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><input type="checkbox" class="captionToggle" id="toggle-https://images.wsj.net/im-829113/?size=custom_1600x1066https://images.wsj.net/im-829113/"> &#39;The Three Shades&#39; at the top of &#39;The Gates of Hell,&#39; Auguste Rodin <span class="imageCredit">Philadelphia Museum of Art</span> </p></div><div class="slide media-object-slideshow-slide" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><img width="undefined" height="undefined" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-829114/?width=600&amp;height=400" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><input type="checkbox" class="captionToggle" id="toggle-https://images.wsj.net/im-829114/?size=custom_1600x1066https://images.wsj.net/im-829114/"> &#39;The Thinker&#39; on &#39;The Gates of Hell,&#39; Auguste Rodin <span class="imageCredit">Philadelphia Museum of Art</span> </p></div><div class="slide media-object-slideshow-slide" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><img width="undefined" height="undefined" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-829118/?width=600&amp;height=400" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><input type="checkbox" class="captionToggle" id="toggle-https://images.wsj.net/im-829118/?size=custom_1600x1066https://images.wsj.net/im-829118/"> Another view of &#39;The Thinker&#39; on &#39;The Gates of Hell,&#39; Auguste Rodin <span class="imageCredit">Philadelphia Museum of Art</span> </p></div><div class="slide media-object-slideshow-slide" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><img width="undefined" height="undefined" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-829115/?width=600&amp;height=400" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><input type="checkbox" class="captionToggle" id="toggle-https://images.wsj.net/im-829115/?size=custom_1600x1066https://images.wsj.net/im-829115/"> &#39;The Falling Man,&#39; one of several casts on &#39;The Gates of Hell,&#39; Auguste Rodin <span class="imageCredit">Philadelphia Museum of Art</span> </p></div><div class="slide media-object-slideshow-slide" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><img width="undefined" height="undefined" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-829117/?width=600&amp;height=400" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><input type="checkbox" class="captionToggle" id="toggle-https://images.wsj.net/im-829117/?size=custom_1600x1066https://images.wsj.net/im-829117/"> &#39;Paolo and Francesca&#39; on &#39;The Gates of Hell,&#39; Auguste Rodin <span class="imageCredit">Philadelphia Museum of Art</span></p></div></amp-carousel></div></div></div><p> From afar, the doors are a grand, rectangular shape, 20 feet tall and 13 feet wide, with intricate forms twisting like vines in the margins of an illuminated manuscript. Up close, they are almost gruesome. A cacophony of human bodies courses through the work. Though some 180 human figures appear, more than 200 were at one point present. Rodin had as his models Lorenzo Ghiberti&#39;s “Gates of Paradise” (1425-52), the bronze doors to the baptistery in Florence, and Michelangelo&#39;s “The Last Judgment” (1535-41). But in the flowing, nonhierarchical portrayal of the contorted bodies of the damned, Rodin made something of his own. There is no end to the dynamic motion of the forms contained within the metal frame. In fact, they appear not to be contained. The souls reach out toward the viewer, pushing beyond the boundaries of the doors. On the upper left, for example, a male figure—“The Falling Man”—hangs upside down like a rock-climber, his muscular arm gripping the lintel. Below him lies a chaotic whirlwind from which he seems determined to escape.</p><p> And though Rodin eventually abandoned a direct representation of Dante&#39;s poem, the sculpture still shows the poet&#39;s influence. Faces and skulls peer out just above Rodin&#39;s most famous work: “The Thinker.” Originally intended to represent Dante himself, the figure later shed specificity, instead symbolizing contemplation.</p><p> Of all the people in the doors, “The Thinker” might be the most static in his pose, but even this piece of “The Gates” demonstrates Rodin&#39;s genius. As the sculptor said: “What makes my Thinker think is that he thinks not only with his brain, with his knitted brow, his distended nostrils and compressed lips, but with every muscle of his arms, back and legs, with his clenched fist and gripping toes.” This physicality echoes in all the figures. Rodin&#39;s expressive manipulation of human anatomy is almost reminiscent of Goya&#39;s paintings. Instead of simply replicating a form he captures the visceral, full force of feeling behind the body. This both defines “The Gates” and explains their importance. Since the Renaissance, art had been a storytelling medium. But here, Rodin abandons the traditional narrative and makes the human form a “story” of its own, using pose and gesture alone to express ideas and emotions—in this case, man&#39;s tragic fate.</p><p> And so, as in Dante&#39;s hell, the damned interact with one another, both helping and harming. A man and a woman, Dante&#39;s Paolo and Francesca, cling to one another, desperate to hold on to the comfort of mutual company. (“The Kiss,” originally part of the doors, was inspired by the tragic lovers too.) To the right of “The Thinker,” panicked souls trample and push. Why the sculptor was heavily criticized during his time is clear: His work is unflinchingly bold, sensual and stylized. For an eternity in which bodies are left behind, Rodin&#39;s hell is startlingly material.</p><p> The way that Rodin composed the “The Gates” broke with artistic convention as well. In places he recycles figures. The “Three Shades” at the top, for example, are casts of the same sculpture, anticipating Picasso&#39;s invention of assemblage—making sculpture out of pre-existing materials.</p><p> Rodin had a devout Catholic upbringing, and briefly joined a religious order after his beloved sister died. Beyond a fantastic depiction of a Dantean or even Christian netherworld, however, “The Gates” are a striking take on human suffering. Through his artistic rebellion, Rodin universalizes the tragedy he captures. The doors are populated not by demons armed with pitchforks, but humans whose unfulfilled longings cause them eternal agony. Created at the turn of the 19th and 20th centuries using sources from the Renaissance, “The Gates of Hell” nonetheless speak to us eloquently today. Admiring them on a fresh autumn day at Philadelphia&#39;s Rodin Museum, as I did nearly two years ago, one must still reckon with an internal hell.</p><p class="articleTagLine"> —Ms. Fischer is a Robert L. Bartley</p> Fellow at the Journal.<p></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 21:45:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/eternal-truths-cast-in-bronze-rodins-the-gates-of-hell-5ea6f0bb</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/eternal-truths-cast-in-bronze-rodins-the-gates-of-hell-5ea6f0bb<category> arts in review</category><category> Art</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>艺术/娱乐</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>Arts in Review</category><category> SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> art</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>艺术</category><category>娱乐</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item></channel></rss>